The most ***awkward*** card I've ever seen, for sure. You, a planeswalker, a being of immense power, able to warp time and reality itself almost at a whim, and one of the few beings able to walk between the many, *many* worlds of the multiverse, is a ***vassal*** to the ***very creatures you summoned into being!?***  

And not only that, the card is practically useless. 1/5, ***at most.***  

@nibelheim\_valesti: The fact that you can summon and bind these *'proper authorities'* to your will should prove that it is rather *they* who are the vassals in these matters, yes? It doesn't matter if you press these creatures into your service by way of magic or respect, as it is still you, the planeswalker, who exerts dominion. And by the way, it is quite obvious that the players are not brazen "neowalkers", but rather the near omnipotent beings that were the planeswalkers from before the events of Time Spiral block.

